narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Easy science credit: do some dense reading for every class and turn in a reading summary, two 10-page papers on two of twenty possible topics. Can get very dry because Bercovici never knows when to stop his own presentation to allow for actual discussion, but he's a very likable guy.
I recommend it if you need a science credit or if you're interested in the topic.
It is a good introduction to many areas of geology and other sciences.

I would recommend Origins of Everything because it is a great seminar. It would be especially good for people needing a science credit. The material throughout the course was incredibly interesting and professor Bercovici was really nice and laid-back.
Absolutely! This class was fun, interesting, and had a manageable workload.
